main event: An unidentified object was observed from the USS ATTU on 21 February 1951, described as cylindrical and lighted, moving at a high speed.
interesting points: The object was approximately 40 to 50 feet in length and observed at a distance of about 7.5 miles., It was moving on a course from northwest to southeast at an estimated speed of 1500 to 2000 knots., The sighting lasted for about 150 seconds before the object disappeared., Weather conditions were clear with unlimited visibility., The object was reported to possibly be a meteor due to insufficient data.
